column5: Would someone recommend a motel or campground in or near Nestor Falls. A Group of us from southern Minnesota are driving up this summer and need a place to bunk for one night. Thanks in advance.
Here is alink that should help you out.http://www.lakeofthewoodsvacations.com/resorts.htm

We have camped at Goose Bay Camp for the last 4 years and will be again this year. There are not a lot of spots but have never had a problem getting one. There is a bath room/shower building close for camper use. The building also has a washer and dryer that you can use when the staff are not using it. Power, water and sewer are available.
I believe there is a provincial park nearby and I recall a resort and motel operation named Helliars.
Arrowhead Camp and Motel, Nestor Falls. Call Clyde or Decie Mason at there winter home in Iowa. 319-436-2907.

Just come and stay in my yard, won't cost you a thing. Just talking about fishing is fine with me and who knows maybe we can help eachother out in the way of fishing srtatagies. I'm not out to make money, just friends.
